<!-- ============================================================ -->
<!-- P.A.N.D.A. FRIENDLY PDA CONVERSATIONS (NON‑TASK) -->
<!-- Procedural Anomaly Narrative Dialogue Architecture -->
<!-- ============================================================ -->
<!--
HOW TO: IMMERSIVE FRIENDLY PDA CONVERSATIONS (LONER)

P.A.N.D.A conversations must be grounded in real game state and real consequences.
No imaginary dialogue: every line should be supportable by trackable mechanics (money,
reputation, goodwill, item transfer, spawned allies/threats, stash reveal, task handoff,
location/time context, rank context, etc.).

1) ID FORMAT + PICKING
- Base key: st_pda_ic_friendly_loner_<id>_<field>
- Turn key: st_pda_ic_friendly_loner_<id>_t<turn>_<field>
- Non-task selection flow:
  a) Script picks friendly/hostile pool.
  b) Script evaluates each available NPC against conversation preconditions.
  c) Conversation is selected with weighted cooldown logic.
- If a precondition references NPC rank, only NPCs with matching rank can be selected.

2) REQUIRED CORE FIELDS
For each conversation ID:
- _open                NPC opener text
- _choice_1..4         Player choices (1..4, stop at first missing)
- _reply_1..4          NPC replies to each choice
- _outcome_1..4        Gameplay effects (or "none")
- _cont_1..4           Optional next turn number (2,3,4...)

For later turns:
- _t2_choice_1, _t2_reply_1, _t2_outcome_1, _t2_cont_1
- _t3_..., _t4_... etc.

3) PLACEHOLDERS (SAFE + IMMERSIVE)
Supported placeholders:
- $player_name
- $npc_name
- $player_faction
- $npc_faction
- $current_level
- $player_money
- $player_rank
- $player_reputation
- $companion_count
- $time_of_day
- $game_hour

Use placeholders to keep messages contextual without inventing fixed story facts.

4) PRECONDITIONS (_precond)
Attach to conversation root ID:
- st_pda_ic_friendly_loner_<id>_precond
- Value is comma-separated commands.

Core player checks:
- req_money:<amount>, req_money_max:<amount>
- req_rank:<rank>, req_rank_max:<rank>
- req_rep:<amount>, req_rep_max:<amount>
- req_kills:<count>, req_mutant_kills:<count>
- req_faction:<fac>, req_not_faction:<fac>
- req_level:<map>, req_not_level:<map>
- req_companions:<n>, req_companions_max:<n>
- req_goodwill:<amount>:<fac>, req_goodwill_max:<amount>:<fac>
- req_has_item:<section>
- req_equipped:<section>, req_equipped_slot:<slot>
- req_achievement:<id>
- req_time_day, req_time_night
- req_health_min:<0..1>, req_health_max:<0..1>

NPC suitability checks (new immersive gate):
- req_npc_rank:<rank>         NPC rank must be >= rank
- req_npc_rank_max:<rank>     NPC rank must be <= rank

Ranks: novice, trainee, experienced, professional, veteran, expert, master, legend.

5) OUTCOMES (_outcome_X)
Comma-separated commands, executed after reply:
- reward_money:<amount>, punish_money:<amount>
- reward_rep:<amount>, punish_rep:<amount>
- reward_gw:<amount>:<fac>, punish_gw:<amount>:<fac>
- give_item:<section>
- courier_item:<section>
- reward_stash
- spawn_companion:<fac>:<delay_s>
- spawn_hostile:<fac>:<delay_s>
- spawn_mutant:<type|random>:<delay_s>
- give_task_cat:<category> (task conversations)

Chance wrapper:
- chance:<percent>:<command>
Example: chance:40:reward_stash

Design rule: outcomes must match what dialogue promises. If the NPC says no payment,
do not grant money; if they promise risk, use chance/spawn outcomes accordingly.

6) TIMEOUTS (NEW)
Each conversation can expire if ignored:
- st_pda_ic_friendly_loner_<id>_timeout      (seconds, real-time)
- st_pda_ic_friendly_loner_<id>_timeout_msg  (NPC annoyed closeout)

If timeout key is absent, script uses a random fallback window.
Use timeout lines that sound like PDA texting cutoffs, not face-to-face roleplay.

7) LORE / IMMERSION RULES
- PDA remote-text tone only (short, practical, uncertain signal context).
- No fixed canon assumptions the player may never have seen.
- No impossible claims without matching mechanics.
- Distinct personalities are good, but must remain plausible for radio/PDA chat.
- Branches should represent meaningful stance: cooperative, cautious, greedy, dismissive.

8) QUICK TEMPLATE
st_pda_ic_friendly_loner_99_open
st_pda_ic_friendly_loner_99_precond
st_pda_ic_friendly_loner_99_choice_1
st_pda_ic_friendly_loner_99_reply_1
st_pda_ic_friendly_loner_99_outcome_1
st_pda_ic_friendly_loner_99_cont_1
... (repeat choice 2..4)
... (add _t2/_t3 branches as needed)
st_pda_ic_friendly_loner_99_timeout
st_pda_ic_friendly_loner_99_timeout_msg
-->

